text:
A fully lasting large creamy tan head tops up a hazy medium brown body. Moderate lacing. No particles. Few small bubbles. Aroma presents malt being light caramel with nuts overtone. Hops are light lemon / lime ... Yeast character is moderate dough. Also, there are evident evocations of plum prune and faint notes of spices and red fruits. Initial flavor is medium sweet (caramel) while development presents spices and cherry. Finish is medium . medium body... oily texture... Lively carbonation... warming alcohol, smooth tartness.

[Bottled ; BB end 05]
[IDLB oct 05}
